[Data by country, area, or territory for 21 Dec 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20DEC21_1640198525.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 32.5% of cases and 19.9% of deaths in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 99.95 million cases. The USA reported 150 238 cases over the last 24 hours. An additional 7 countries/territories reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Brazil, Argentina, Colombia, Peru, Puerto Rico, Bolivia, and Chile), while 4 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases (Mexico, Ecuador, Panama, Trinidad & Tobago). Costa Rica and Canada, among others, did not report any cases.

- The European region reported 53.7% of daily case numbers and 60.9% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 95.08 million cases. Some countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (5 cases), Sweden, and Switzerland (14 cases), among others. A total of 25 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, with 9 reporting more than 10 000, 16 reporting over 1000 cases, and an additional 6 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 1.9% of daily case numbers and 2.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 17.03 million cases. Jordan (3578) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours, followed by Iran (2390) and Lebanon (1479). Lebanon, Egypt, and Libya reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 5.0% of daily case numbers and 2.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.83 million cases. South Africa (8511) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours, followed by Botswana (4837), Mozambique (2346), Zimbabwe (2283), Nigeria (1368), Eswatini (1110), and Kenya (1020). Uganda, Zambia, and Ethiopia reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases over the last 24 hours. A total of 15 countries/territories did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 5.2% of daily case numbers and 5.7% deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.88 million cases. Viet Nam (14 977) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours, followed by South Korea, Australia, Malaysia, and Laos.

- The South-East Asia region reported 1.5% of the daily newly reported cases and 7.6% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 44.84 million cases. India is dominant, reporting 5326 cases during the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (2476). Nepal (252) and Indonesia (216) reported fewer than 500 cases over the last 24 hours. Bangladesh, Myanmar, Maldives, and Sri Lanka, among others, did not report cases for many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 21 Dec 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod. UBA]

